<doc id="627006" wikidata="Q7537750" url="?curid=627006" title="Skyhook (boarding)">
<text>In skateboarding and related sports, skyhooks are devices which serve as semi-open bindings. They are usually made of aluminium, steel or hard plastic and are formed to cover the rider&#x27;s boot, yet to allow him to easily free his feet from the hook. They may be screwed to the top of the board to facilitate jumping and enhance stability during a ride.

They are mostly used on freeboards and longboards without a kicktail.</text><links>
